12:
What's all the grumbling for, Inaho?
Everything okay?
16:
NO! I-I was so trendy, so why am I
not popular yet?
20:
I did everything the magazine said
and more! So why did I not receive a
single present?!
24:
...Well, to be fair, I did find this stuff
addressed to me, but...
28:
Wait, you got ALL of this? And that
isn't enough?
31:
Mmm... I dunno. I found them laid
out near the entrance of our shrine,
but they all had cards with prayers
attached.
37:
Things like, "Benevolent nine-tailed
fox, please bless our village with
fruitful harvests."
45:
Exactly! And, and... someone had the
GALL to ask for love and a happy
marriage.
49:
If I could magically give people
boyfriends then I. WOULD NOT. BE
SINGLE!
60: I suppose I knew all along...
63:
Somewhere in my heart, I
understood Santa's popularity was
not the kind I wanted, but I clung to
it anyways.
66:
Yeah... I mean, no one thinks about
asking Santa out on a date...
Probably.
84:
It's embarrassing to admit, but I
think deep-down, everyone wants to
be the star of their story.
88: Everyone wants to be... the star?
98:
Forget about it, Stella. That is
enough moping for one day!
A-ahem. I, um, I...
101: I have presents for both of you!
104:
Y-you know, friend presents! The,
um, "like" like kind, not the "LIKE" like...
117:
And we also have presents for you,
which means... Drumroll please!
121: I get to swap presents with you!
126:
Here, Stella. Peaches from a secret
mythical spring!
132:
They are said to be so sweet,
anyone who eats them becomes
sweet and saintly too!
136:
Not that you need it.\n
But I hope you like them!
141:
I do. Thank you, Inaho. They look
delicious.
145:
Next up is Alk! I made your present
out of a branch from the top of an
ancient, sacred tree in Mother's
shrine.
157:
What do you think? Just imagine all
the things you can make!
161:
I-I think it's great! Way more
practical than what I was afraid—\n
I mean, ahem... Thanks, Inaho!
165:
All right, my turn. Here you are!
Happy holidays!
170: Wow! Hair oil? It smells so goooood!
173:
Yup, it's made with the forest sprites'
favorite herbs and flowers. Perfect
for both hair and fur!
177:
I cannot wait to try it!\n
I can always trust you to be in the
loop on girly girl stuff, Alk!
181: Hm? What is this second bag?
185: That's from me. Open it up.
190:
WHOOOOA! These are the cutest
earrings I have ever seen!
198:
I love them, Stella!\n
Forget the popular trends, THIS is my
style!
201:
I'm glad you love them.\n
I hope they are trendy too, though.
207:
This is the best day ever! Thank you
both so, so, so much!
211:
Stella, Alk, I actually have one more
thing for you.
218: Wow, the view up here is amazing!
225:
I read about winter illuminations in
the Oculus.
229:
I waited until the big day so we
could see the lights together under
the stars!
233:
Happy memories are the best
holiday present of all, right?
238:
Nuh-uh, no thank yous yet!\n
We are only just getting started!
241:
People wish upon shooting stars, do
they not?
246:
I wish that we can stargaze together
like this again some time.
251: Ooh, that's a good one! Me too!
260:
A small feat for Princess Inaho
Tamamo, yokai Santa!
262:
Stars above, heed our wishes and
dance for us tonight!
265:
Behold the golden power of Nine
Tails—Stardrop Snowglobe!
269:
I've never seen snow that glows
before... Hey, wait. Are these—
271:
STAAAAARS! Look at all the shooting
stars!
